Content:
This could be interesting.  One would have to define what hash math should mean.  Personally, I would expect (based on my naive assumptions here) that:<p><pre><code>    {1: &quot;A&quot;} + {} == {1: &quot;A&quot;}
</code></pre>
but<p><pre><code>    {1: &quot;A&quot;} + {} + {1: &quot;B&quot;, 2: &quot;Z&quot;} + {1: &quot;C&quot;} + {}
</code></pre>
should reduce to:<p><pre><code>    {1: (&quot;A&quot; + &quot;B&quot; + &quot;C&quot;), 2: &quot;Z&quot;}
</code></pre>
Whether you can add &quot;A&quot;, &quot;B&quot;, and &quot;C&quot; would depend on string functions (could be &quot;ABC&quot; or raise an exception that these cannot be added for example).
